props.text:
After completing this module, are you able to do the following?

  • Define what a bar graph is and explain how it is used to represent data.
  • Identify the key components of a bar graph (title, labels, axes, scales, bars).
  • Construct a bar graph from a given set of data, ensuring accurate scaling and labeling.
  • Interpret and analyze bar graphs to draw conclusions and make comparisons between data sets.

If you are ready to move on, continue onto the next module!

If you need additional support, go back and review module content and reach out to your teacher for help!
